ving, providing resources like money/meals)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "I am open",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Funny",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Adventurous",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Open-minded",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Experiencing new things",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "25 - 36",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,78);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(39,63,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I just moved back to Charlotte and I saw this event on TikTok! It is more difficult to make friends when you\u2019re getting older because you care very much about values.",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "10",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "N/A",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "I am specifically looking for people who are currently working on their emotional health and their healing. People who know how to directly communicate, while also being kind and can be silly.",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Consistency builds trust. This goes for everything from communication and behavior. Showing up can either be emotional or physical and the way someone shows up consistently also is what builds trust. Being able to take accountability and be vulnerable is very important.",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Somewhere in between \u2013 depends on the vibe",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I prefer concrete plans with minimal wiggle room",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Texting throughout the day",\n    "Mix of everything/I''m flexible"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Need time to process before I am ready to discuss",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Quality time together to reconnect",\n    "Written communication (text, letter, etc)",\n    "Acts of care and presence",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\n    "Time and space before reconnecting",\n    "Humor and lightness to ease back in"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Set a boundary:",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "5",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am learning how to set them, but it''s still hard",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "I have noticed that most of my past friends don\u2019t really put an effort to get to know me or spend time with me. And I\u2019m very proud of myself for not continuously staying in those people\u2019s lives. And I\u2019m actively working on boundary setting and making sure that I respect myself",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Hiking/nature walks",\n    "Writing (journaling, poetry, books)",\n    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\n    "Learning new skills",\n    "Writing and reflection",\n    "Activism and social change",\n    "Meditation/mindfulness",\n    "Therapy/personal growth work",\n    "Nature connection and grounding",\n    "Energy work/holistic practices"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Adventure",\n    "Creativity",\n    "Fun",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Growth",\n    "Loyalty",\n    "Non-conformity",\n    "Self-awareness",\n    "Self-expression",\n    "Uniqueness"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "Friendship is about celebrating each other''s wins",\n    "I value reliability and follow-through",\n    "Mutual effort and reciprocity matters to me"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\n    "Consistency and reliability",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Adventure and new experiences",\n    "Peaceful, easy presence"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Honest and transparent (direct communicator), can be silly or serious depending on the situation, and works on their emotional health (has self respect and self love).",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "A dealbreaker for me is a woman who does not see an issue with capitalism or patriarchy, and another dealbreaker would be someone who has a difficult time being honest, transparent and consistent.",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)",\n    "Other forms of support (problem-solving, providing resources like money/meals)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Once a week",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Primarily in-person connections",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Unique",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Caring",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Adventurous",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Reciprocity with care, consideration, and adventure",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": [\n    "Woman",\n    "Non-binary"\n  ],\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "25-45, woman or non binary.",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,NULL);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(40,65,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "A lot of my long term friends (10+ years) have moved away. I started hosting events to make friends with Charlotte Young And Social 20s-40s but hosting takes a lot out of me and I don\u2019t get to have many genuine conversations or make lasting connections. I love hosting events, but long term connections are what I\u2019m looking for, not just seeing someone at one event, having good conversation and thinking a friendship could be there, then never seeing that person again.",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "8",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Good capacity (I''m ready to prioritize friendships)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "Grief or loss",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "I am AuDHD so making connections deeper than passing conversation feels hard even though I\u2019ve been told people gravitate toward me.",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Openness, vulnerability, fun times, hanging out ranging from going out and trying new things and experiences to just hanging out and watching movies",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Share openly and engage actively with most people",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Phone calls",\n    "Primarily in-person hangouts"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Address it directly and as soon as possible",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\n    "Time and space before reconnecting"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Stay curious and check in:",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "5",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I struggle with boundaries and often overextend",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "Everybody is busy and life gets in the way. Attachments styles can clash and sincere apologies go a long way.",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Hiking/nature walks",\n    "Dancing (salsa, pole, aerial, casual, etc)",\n    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\n    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\n    "Learning new skills",\n    "Writing and reflection",\n    "Activism and social change",\n    "Therapy/personal growth work",\n    "Nature connection and grounding",\n    "Other"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests_other_text": "Pole fitness",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Being: I prefer hanging out or just existing in each other''s presence",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Empathy",\n    "Creativity",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Trust",\n    "Independence",\n    "Passion",\n    "Self-awareness",\n    "Self-expression",\n    "Uniqueness",\n    "Sexuality"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "I appreciate friends who respect my need for space",\n    "Friends should challenge me to grow",\n    "Humor and laughter are essential to friendship"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Intellectual stimulation",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Adventure and new experiences",\n    "Peaceful, easy presence"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Openness, respect, shared interest, genuine people",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Gossiping about each other behind the other person\u2019s back, breaking trust, possessiveness",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)",\n    "Other forms of support (problem-solving, providing resources like money/meals)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Once a week",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Primarily in-person connections",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Honest",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Unique",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Open",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Support, mutual connection, depth",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "27-35",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,50);
