learning how to set them, but it''s still hard",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "I tend to be avoidant but dedicated to my friends",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Hiking/nature walks",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\n    "Volunteering/advocacy",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Reading (fiction, non-fiction, audiobooks)",\n    "Activism and social change",\n    "Astrology"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Doing: I love activities, adventures, and experiences with friends",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Independence",\n    "Community",\n    "Stability"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": "I value friends who share my worldview and values",\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Mutual support during hard times",\n    "Celebration of wins and joys",\n    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\n    "Consistency and reliability",\n    "Adventure and new experiences"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Someone who is consistent and reliable",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Flaky, political views don\u2019t align",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Other forms of support (problem-solving, providing resources like money/meals)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Quality over quantity \u2013 frequency matters less than depth",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Reliable",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Independent",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Open",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "I would like to receive support or a connection. Someone to explore with!",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": [\n    "Woman",\n    "Non-binary"\n  ],\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "24-30",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,145);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(86,131,replace('{\012  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I\u2019ve been moving around forever and between that and having my wonderful daughter 5 years ago, I haven\u2019t made any meaningful connections. It\u2019s lonely!",\012  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Leftist",\012  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\012  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "I\u2019m awkward and can\u2019t read a room but I promise I\u2019m a good time. \nI\u2019m not real close with my family because of distance so I\u2019m not sure how they\u2019d describe me. Despite that I\u2019m a wearer of many hats. I love to hobby collect. I like to garden \ud83c\udf43 iykyk and sit in the sun. Or watch funny movies. I play the piano and ukulele. I\u2019m pretty open minded and am just happy to be included most of the time. I like nature, shopping, coffee, thrifting, going on random adventures etc. idk where I am exactly politically but I\u2019m pretty left leaning I guess. I watch a lot of political commentary when I\u2019m cleaning and stuff.",\012  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "8",\012  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\012  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\012  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\012  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": [\012    "Recent/upcoming move",\012    "Health challenges",\012    "New parent/caregiving responsibilities"\012  ],\012  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "I\u2019m on the spectrum so I need some coaxing sometimes. I don\u2019t really have a good awareness of how hard I\u2019m going so I overdo it with work and social stuff until I can\u2019t anymore and have to hermit for a few days to a week. I\u2019m a devoted person with a big heart and I am very dependable. But socially keep this in mind!",\012  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Showing up to me is being there. Giving your energy in whatever way (positively). Listening to someone vent or coming over to help clean. Community I guess. It\u2019s a lot of things that you put in that work together to make this happen.",\012  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "2",\012  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "I''m quiet at first but warm up over time",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "1",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "3",\012  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\012  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\012    "Texting throughout the day",\012    "Mix of everything/I''m flexible"\012  ],\012  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\012  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Get overwhelmed and withdraw",\012  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\012    "A direct conversation about what happened",\012    "Acts of care and presence",\012    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\012    "Humor and lightness to ease back in"\012  ],\012  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Stay curious and check in:",\012  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "3",\012  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I struggle with boundaries and often overextend",\012  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "I\u2019m flaky because I have a driving phobia and feel weird asking my husband for rides since he drives a lot. \nAlso I\u2019ve struggled with withdrawing a lot and it\u2019s come across as also flaky. I\u2019d give dumb reasons that didn\u2019t make sense and I\u2019ve had friendships end because I was appearing so shady. I\u2019ve worked on that and still am",\012  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\012    "Hiking/nature walks",\012    "Yoga/Pilates",\012    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\012    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\012    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\012    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\012    "Book clubs or discussion groups",\012    "Volunteering/advocacy",\012    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\012    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\012    "Reading (fiction, non-fiction, audiobooks)",\012    "Podcasts and documentaries",\012    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\012    "Learning new skills",\012    "Writing and reflection",\012    "Activism and social change",\012    "Meditation/mindfulness",\012    "Tarot/oracle cards",\012    "Astrology",\012    "Religious gatherings (temple/church/mosque, etc)",\012    "Therapy/personal growth work",\012    "Nature connection and grounding",\012    "Energy work/holistic practices",\012    "Medicinal herbs/substances"\012  ],\012  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I don\u2019t like super crowded places that are hard to navigate lol. I think I mentioned earlier I play music and like to chill or be in nature. I\u2019m not much of a drinker but I garden",\012  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\012  "values_top_values": [\012    "Activism",\012    "Empathy",\012    "Nature",\012    "Fun",\012    "Genuineness",\012    "Spirituality",\012    "Honesty",\012    "Love",\012    "Self-awareness",\012    "Self-expression"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\012    "Friendship is about celebrating each other''s wins",\012    "Friends should challenge me to grow",\012    "I value friends who share my worldview and values"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\012    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\012    "Shared laughter and lightness",\012    "Mutual support during hard times",\012    "Celebration of wins and joys",\012    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\012    "Consistency and reliability",\012    "Genuineness",\012    "Peaceful, easy presence"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "No maga! I\u2019m not religious but I\u2019m spiritual. Idc what you practice as long as our values align.",\012  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "I\u2019m not sure. Any bigotedness? Not being open minded. Not being honest or understanding.",\012  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\012    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\012    "Physical touch (hugging, holding hands)",\012    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)"\012  ],\012  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Quality over quantity \u2013 frequency matters less than depth",\012  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Chill",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Understanding",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Weird",\012  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Support! Mutual support. Listening to each other and genuine connection.",\012  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": [\012    "Woman",\012    "Non-binary"\012  ],\012  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "Similar to me 28-38\nI\u2019m 32. But I\u2019m not strict about those margins. I just think I would resonate better with that age range or older",\012  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\012    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\012    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\012  ]\012}','\012',char(10)),1,138);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(87,132,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "Looking to make friends and learn how to engage with people more!",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Liberal",\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "Quite at first, but will open up and start talking after a while. Friend say that I\u2019m reserved.",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "8",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Good capacity (I''m ready to prioritize friendships)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Being able to be present for a person and sometimes just being a listening ear to a person where the can vent!",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Observe, listen deeply, and engage selectively",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I need structure and advanced notice",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": "Mix of everything/I''m flexible",\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Prefer to avoid direct confrontation if possible",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Written communication (text, letter, etc)",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Stay curious and check in:",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "4",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am rigid with my boundaries, sometimes to a fault",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "It\u2019s always been me that has the start of the discourse and with being in therapy for over 3+ years. I\u2019m working on being more communicative and not jumping to conclusions and realising that people have lives and other commitments not just our friendship.",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Dancing (salsa, pole, aerial, casual, etc)",\n    "Sports (playing or watching)",\n    "Writing (journaling, poetry, books)",\n    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Fashion/Styling",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Podcasts and documentaries",\n    "Learning new skills",\n    "Meditation/mindfulness",\n    "Therapy/personal growth work"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I\u2019m open to learning and trying new things.",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Health",\n    "Forgiveness",\n    "Growth",\n    "Trust",\n    "Self-awareness"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "Friends should be able to have difficult conversations",\n    "Friendship is about celebrating each other''s wins",\n    "Friends should challenge me to grow"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Mutual support during hard times",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Non-judgment and acceptance"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Not sure how to answer that, because I have to think about my boundaries.",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "No lie, not respect time and just lazy",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Words of affirmation (encouragement, posts about you)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Multiple times per week",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Sense of humour",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Patient",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Consistent",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Someone who respects boundaries",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "Similar in age to me 40-60 years old",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),0,NULL);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(88,134,replace('{\012  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "So I\u2019m just looking for new friends cause I tried at UNCC but no luck",\012  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Moderate",\012  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\012  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "I have a bachelors degree in communications. I wanna work in healthcare and I am someone who is loyal and also extroverted",\012  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "10",\012  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Abundant capacity (I have space, time, and energy to invest)",\012  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\012  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "I don''t think I have significant friendship wounds",\012  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "N/A",\012  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\012  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Someone who will give me the time of day and hang out with me and talk to me. Also someone who would be willing to help me feel emotionally safe too",\012  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "4",\012  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Somewhere in between \u2013 depends on the vibe",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "3",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "2",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "1",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "4",\012  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\012  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\012    "Primarily in-person hangouts",\012    "Mix of everything/I''m flexible"\012  ],\012  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\012  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Address it directly and as soon as possible",\012  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\012    "A direct conversation about what happened",\012    "Quality time together to reconnect",\012    "Written communication (text, letter, etc)",\012    "Acts of care and presence"\012  ],\012  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Address it directly:",\012  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "3",\012  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am clear and direct about my boundaries.",\012  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "If someone says that they\u2019ll do something for you but not do it. That tells me everything that I need to know or if they become too pushy it\u2019s time to leave",\012  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\012    "Dancing (salsa, pole, aerial, casual, etc)",\012    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\012    "Cooking/Baking",\012    "Fashion/Styling",\012    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\012    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\012    "Tarot/oracle cards",\012    "Astrology",\012    "Video games (PC, PS, XBOX, Switch)"\012  ],\012  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I am a tarot reader and I like to go out and explore new places and have fun",\012  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Doing: I love activities, adventures, and experiences with friends",\012  "values_top_values": [\012    "Beauty",\012    "Career",\012    "Harmony",\012    "Empathy",\012    "Creativity",\012    "Fulfillment",\012    "Spirituality",\012    "Community",\012    "Intuition",\012    "Love"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\012    "Friendship is about celebrating each other''s wins",\012    "I value friends who check in consistently",\012    "Mutual effort and reciprocity matters to me"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\012    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\012    "Mutual support during hard times",\012    "Celebration of wins and joys",\012    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\012    "Consistency and reliability",\012    "Genuineness",\012    "Adventure and new experiences"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Must be reliable and also not be fake and also withstand me talking like an idiot at times. Also give me the respect that I give you. If we have an issue we talk about it and not cut each other off without talking about it",\012  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Too bossy or can\u2019t talk about what I did wrong if I did.\nI sometimes don\u2019t know and I can\u2019t stand someone who is always negative",\012  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\012    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\012    "Physical touch (hugging, holding hands)",\012    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)"\012  ],\012  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Multiple times per week",\012  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Honest",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Kind",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Fun",\012  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Loyalty and someone who won\u2019t leave me when things get rough",\012  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\012  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "Similar age to me which is 24 but no older than 29",\012  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\012    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\012    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\012  ]\012}','\012',char(10)),0,NULL);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(89,135,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I like meeting people naturally but it feels like every time I met a girl and I think we will become friends, I get ghosted and they have their own friends already and are not really open to more friends. So, I don\u2019t really go out anymore and therefore, cannot make friends I normally would.",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Apolitical",\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "Sweet, Caring, Talkative, Ride or Die Type, Outgoing, Trustworthy, Upstander",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "7",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "I am actively working on it now",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "Health challenges",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "I can be a bit insecure about myself and it\u2019s not to fish for compliments, it\u2019s because I used to be this super confident bold girl and now I barely take pictures anymore. I love being friends with anyone but one of my biggest pet peeves is women who can\u2019t be friends with who we are still working on building their confidence back up.",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Showing up for me looks like encouraging me to be my best self, showing up for the small accomplishments and events I would plan to go to, not being judgy at all, and paying attention to things about me that a friend would know.",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Share openly and engage actively with most people",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I need structure and advanced notice",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Video calls",\n    "Mix of everything/I''m flexible"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Quick responder, love ongoing conversations",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Address it directly and as soon as possible",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Quality time together to reconnect",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\n    "Humor and lightness to ease back in"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Pull back and wait to see if they reach out or notice",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "3",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "It depends on the friendship",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "Patterns I\u2019ve noticed about myself is I can be defensive when I feel I am under attack. When someone is bringing up multiple things I\u2019ve done that\u2019s bothered them, that would make me upset because I feel like I\u2019m an easy going person to talk to so why not address it then and there? Another pattern I\u2019ve noticed is my friend can feel like they are in competition and/or I feel superior to them but that is not the case. I\u2019m just very proud of where I am and like to express that and I like to help others and encourage them to get where they need to be.",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Dancing (salsa, pole, aerial, casual, etc)",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Cooking/Baking",\n    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Reading (fiction, non-fiction, audiobooks)",\n    "Learning new skills",\n    "Other"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests_other_text": "Researching things I\u2019m passionate about and Traveling.",\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I\u2019m always open to new things and I prefer to do things with others but I can do it alone as well.",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Ambition",\n    "Fun",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Honesty",\n    "Trust",\n    "Loyalty",\n    "Order",\n    "Passion",\n    "Stability",\n    "Work Ethic"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "Friends should challenge me to grow",\n    "Humor and laughter are essential to friendship",\n    "Mutual effort and reciprocity matters to me"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Intellectual stimulation",\n    "Mutual support during hard times",\n    "Celebration of wins and joys",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\n    "Consistency and reliability",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Adventure and new experiences",\n    "Peaceful, easy presence"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Openness, Honesty, Reciprocity, Accountability and Genuineness",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Someone who plays victim, judgy people, someone talks behind my back or says \u201cI\u2019m too much\u201d instead of respectfully letting me know they need space because they are overstimulated, someone who acts different around certain people and someone who would leave me in a uncomfortable or dangerous situation.",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)",\n    "Other forms of support (problem-solving, providing resources like money/meals)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "I am open",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Genuine",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Caring",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Outgoing",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "I would like to receive someone who understands that yes life happens but you still show up because you can expect I would do the same if need be.",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "21-35",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,67);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(90,136,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I saw the event on TikTok and thought it would be a good event for someone who recently moved to Charlotte like myself.",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Liberal",\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Man",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "I am someone who can be considered an introvert due to my quiet and aloof nature. However, once someone gets to know me, I am very talkative. I can as say I\u2019m funny (at times). Conversations are most enjoyable through jokes, in my opinion. I like to talk about the deeper things in life, especially through lessons I learn in the books read.",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "8",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am open to friendships, but want to take it slow",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "N/A",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "I believe showing up for a friend looks like being able to spend quality time with them, even spontaneously. I want consistency with reaching out to one another. It\u2019s hard for me to consider someone a friend if I always have to reach out first. I also like being friends with someone who will push me to grow because I would do the same for them. A friend of mine should be willing to make changes on constructive feedback I may have if there\u2019s an issue with the dynamic. I enjoy friendships where one is comfortable being vulnerable with their issues but willing to take action if possible after a conversation is had on how we talk about how to move forward.",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Observe, listen deeply, and engage selectively",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I prefer concrete plans with minimal wiggle room",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Video calls",\n    "Primarily in-person hangouts"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Need time to process before I am ready to discuss",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Pull back and wait to see if they reach out or notice",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "3",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am rigid with my boundaries, sometimes to a fault",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "I noticed that I took too long to confront an issue I may have had in old friendships. I now work on saying my issues in the moment and within a short time frame. My friendship breakups have been a slow burn and more severe because I withheld feelings longer than I needed to. I feel like I rushed into closeness in some previous friendships and the closeness would scare me and I would fall back. I now ease my way into friendship to make sure I can handle being close to someone.",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Yoga/Pilates",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Reading (fiction, non-fiction, audiobooks)",\n    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\n    "Astrology",\n    "Therapy/personal growth work",\n    "Other"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests_other_text": "Going to random pop up events",\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I\u2019m starting to get into producing beats. Rap/Rnb/Afrobeats/Other African genres",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Peace",\n    "Fun",\n    "Fulfillment",\n    "Growth",\n    "Honesty",\n    "Independence",\n    "Intuition",\n    "Integrity",\n    "Purpose",\n    "Sexuality"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "I value friends who check in consistently",\n    "Friends should challenge me to grow",\n    "I value friends who share my worldview and values"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Intellectual stimulation",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Consistency and reliability",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Adventure and new experiences",\n    "Peaceful, easy presence"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "I need integrity, respect, receptiveness, intelligence, humor, easygoingness, peace, and interdependence",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Dealbreakers are inconsistencies, lying, lack of accountability, being over emotional, lack of respecting boundaries, debby downers and being unreceptive to change.",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Words of affirmation (encouragement, posts about you)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Quality over quantity \u2013 frequency matters less than depth",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Funny",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Caring",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Intellectual",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "I would want to receive fulfillment and joy. I also want to be able to be challenged to grow. I want to be able to find people who are dependable and I can trust.",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "Woman",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "22-26, a similar age to me (24)",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,151);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(91,137,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I have done a lot of work in therapy (shout out Nicole who suggested this to me) and have let go of some harmful friendship that weren\u2019t healthy. I find myself a bit lonely although I have a good support system. I\u2019m looking for friends with similar hobbies and interests that want to do exciting things together. I am a very deep and attentive person and want a deep and genuine connection with someone who I can be silly and authentic with. I am used to having a lot of friends and am recently semi-sober (just working on being okay without having to drink socially) so I would love to build up a community that is based on shared interests/values rather than \u201cgoing out\u201d.",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Liberal",\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "I\u2019m very outgoing, most people describe me as very funny (leaning towards more asshole-ish humor but in an endearing way), and I\u2019m extremely loyal and attentive. I have ADHD and have been known to be \u201cloud\u201d and eccentric. I have calmed down in recent years but I still love to get excited about the topics I\u2019m interested in a nerd out/ be a little dramatic. I would be described as a girls\u2019 girl I believe. I\u2019m very liberal because I was raised by immigrants and am generally interested in world news, travel, other cultures. I am a bit of a music \u201csnob\u201d (I just love to nerd out over it) and love movies and TV shows (mostly thrillers, psychological dramas, drama, and dystopian sci-fi). People would describe me as generally easy to get along with but I have also been told I am intimidating at first because I have such a big personality. I am a Scorpio and live up to most of the stereotypes.",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "8",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "I am actively working on it now",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "I am not a big texter right off the bat which has bothered people before so I think that is important to note how I do not show up. I am big on quality time and prioritize planning and spending time together. I love to speak deeply and honestly about what\u2019s going on in other peoples lives and am a great listener and advice giver. Having long conversations, planning and attending trips, getting to know the people special to them, and hosting dinners are some of the things I do to show up.",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Share openly and engage actively with most people",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Occasional meaningful texts",\n    "Primarily in-person hangouts"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Prefer to avoid direct confrontation if possible",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "Quality time together to reconnect",\n    "Acts of care and presence"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Feel hurt but not saying anything, hoping it doesn''t happen again",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "3",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am learning how to set them, but it''s still hard",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "I need to stop bottling up my resentment. I need to be clear on boundaries. I have made friends in the past out of convenience, proximity, and bad habits which I am learning not to do. Need to be intentional about making friends and choose more wisely. I let people use me and cross boundaries/\u201coverstay their welcome\u201d. I have people pleasing tendencies because I genuinely always want others to feel comfortable around me. These are all things I have been working on and have made strides in. I usually end friendships after bottling up all of my grievances for years and then they do one last thing that really crosses a boundary for me. The last time this happened I had been actively setting boundaries and the friend got upset and continues to cross them out of almost entitlement(?) to my time. I often attract codependent relationships which I recognize go both ways so I am steering away from that. In the past it\u2019s been an all or nothing, \u201cwhen I\u2019m done, I\u2019m done\u201d approach with friendships",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Hiking/nature walks",\n    "Yoga/Pilates",\n    "Rock climbing/adventure sports",\n    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Cooking/Baking",\n    "Fashion/Styling",\n    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Podcasts and documentaries",\n    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\n    "Learning new skills",\n    "Therapy/personal growth work",\n    "Nature connection and grounding"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I love to ski and would love to have friends that ski or are open to learning (I used to be an instructor). I am prioritizing connecting with nature and would love someone who is down to enjoy camping, hiking, fly fishing, white water rafting, or rock climbing. I am a huge music buff and love to listen and analyze with my friends. I like every kind of music except for pop country (this excludes bluegrass, blues country, etc.) I love to cook and host dinner parties often.",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Empathy",\n    "Nature",\n    "Fulfillment",\n    "Trust",\n    "Loyalty",\n    "Love",\n    "Passion",\n    "Resilience",\n    "Self-awareness",\n    "Uniqueness"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "Friends should challenge me to grow",\n    "Humor and laughter are essential to friendship",\n    "Mutual effort and reciprocity matters to me"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Intellectual stimulation",\n    "Mutual support during hard times",\n    "Consistency and reliability",\n    "Genuineness"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "I get along with people who have different political opinions and spiritual values but I would not consider them for a good friend. I would prefer people who are left leaning and not religious. I want to be able to be authentic and speak about my world views openly. It is not a deal-breaker but would love to meet someone who also values music very highly and loves to explore it. I do not want to be friends with someone whose main interest is going out to drink, although I enjoy doing that maybe once per month.",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Someone who doesn\u2019t like to \u201cgossip\u201d. Not in a negative way, but I like to get the low down on others as a way of checking in and mutually confirming our perceptions. I think it is harmless as long as it is not coming from a judgmental perspective. I had noticed a lot of people frown upon this type of talk and get uncomfortable with it. I genuinely just like to \u201cbeat a dead horse\u201d and \u201cyap\u201d if that makes sense.",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "A few times a month",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Primarily in-person connections",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Funny",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Confident",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Genuine",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "I want someone who is down to spend quality time with me and accept me for who I am and who I am becoming. I am on a healing and health journey and want someone to respect that. I want someone who is down to have a talk with me once in a while if I\u2019m feeling down or need to vent. I would like someone who is interested in trying new activities with me outdoors. I want a deep, healthy emotional connection where we can bond over our interests and inside jokes and accept each other.",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "Woman",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "25-40",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),0,NULL);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(92,138,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I haven\u2019t really found a community since moving here and friends have been hard to make as well.",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Prefer not to say",\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "Im a mix of extrovert and introvert. I like to go on adventures, travel and have the occasional night out. I like game nights, hanging out at a coffee shop or a bookstore and thrifting. But I also like lazy days on the couch watching tv or just reading a book. I\u2019m a very reliable friend that will always be there for people day or night. I don\u2019t need fixed plans and can go with the flow.",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "9",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I would like casual connections that could grow naturally over time",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "I don''t think I have significant friendship wounds",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "Other",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_other_text": "My partner is deployed in the Middle East so it can be stressful at times.",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Just making an effort really. Life gets busy but it\u2019s always nice knowing people want you around be it a little escape to grab coffee, checking in, or even just sending a meme.",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Somewhere in between \u2013 depends on the vibe",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Texting throughout the day",\n    "Mix of everything/I''m flexible"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Quick responder, love ongoing conversations",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Address it directly and as soon as possible",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\n    "Humor and lightness to ease back in"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Pull back and wait to see if they reach out or notice",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "4",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "It depends on the friendship",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "Not all friendships work out and that\u2019s ok.",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Running/Cycling",\n    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\n    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\n    "Book clubs or discussion groups",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Reading (fiction, non-fiction, audiobooks)",\n    "Podcasts and documentaries",\n    "Tarot/oracle cards",\n    "Astrology",\n    "Video games (PC, PS, XBOX, Switch)",\n    "Other"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests_other_text": "Movies",\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I like to make candles and occasionally sell at markets.",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Adventure",\n    "Empathy",\n    "Creativity",\n    "Animals",\n    "Fun",\n    "Generosity",\n    "Spirituality",\n    "Trust",\n    "Community",\n    "Uniqueness"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "I value reliability and follow-through",\n    "Humor and laughter are essential to friendship",\n    "Mutual effort and reciprocity matters to me"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Mutual support during hard times",\n    "Celebration of wins and joys",\n    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\n    "Adventure and new experiences",\n    "Peaceful, easy presence"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "I\u2019m not religious in the least. I respect people\u2019s choices in practices but I\u2019m very uncomfortable when it comes to organized religions like Christians, Mormons etc. I myself am more Pagan and that does not aline well with most people here in the south. I\u2019m a witch and proud of it.",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Religion",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)",\n    "Gifts (items that remind them of you)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Quality over quantity \u2013 frequency matters less than depth",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Kind",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Weird",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Adventurous",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "A sense of connection. I\u2019ve been so isolated since moving here. I want to find joy in things again. I find myself just doing the same things alone and it can get lonely fast.",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,147);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(93,142,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I heard about it from someone and they sent me a link",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": [\n    "Liberal",\n    "Leftist"\n  ],\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Man",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "I''m someone who''s relaxed and and witty and can make people laugh.",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "9",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "I am actively working on it now",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": [\n    "Ending a significant relationship",\n    "Other"\n  ],\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_other_text": "Working on self",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "No",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "Being able for someone to relate to me",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Somewhere in between \u2013 depends on the vibe",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Texting throughout the day",\n    "Primarily in-person hangouts"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Get overwhelmed and withdraw",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Quality time together to reconnect",\n    "Acts of care and presence",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\n    "Time and space before reconnecting",\n    "Humor and lightness to ease back in"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Stay curious and check in:",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "3",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am learning how to set them, but it''s still hard",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "I have to be careful with what I say and to who. I need to be protective of myself and to not get stuck in a bad situation.",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Hiking/nature walks",\n    "Running/Cycling",\n    "Writing (journaling, poetry, books)",\n    "Cooking/Baking",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Meditation/mindfulness",\n    "Therapy/personal growth work",\n    "Video games (PC, PS, XBOX, Switch)"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "No",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "It depends",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Health",\n    "Fun",\n    "Forgiveness",\n    "Growth",\n    "Inclusiveness",\n    "Purpose",\n    "Self-awareness"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "Friends should be able to have difficult conversations",\n    "Friends should challenge me to grow",\n    "Friends should accept me exactly as I am"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Intellectual stimulation",\n    "Mutual support during hard times",\n    "Celebration of wins and joys",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Non-judgment and acceptance",\n    "Consistency and reliability",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Adventure and new experiences",\n    "Peaceful, easy presence"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Understanding, forgiveness, humor, kindness",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Unreliable, judgmental, quick to rush",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)",\n    "Other forms of support (problem-solving, providing resources like money/meals)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Multiple times per week",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Primarily in-person connections",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Good",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Fair",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Relatable",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Belonging",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "Somewhere between 25 and 45",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,118);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(94,143,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "Just curious to meet new people , recently new to the south",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Leftist",\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "Creative, sarcastic, and giving",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "7",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Good capacity (I''m ready to prioritize friendships)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I would like casual connections that could grow naturally over time",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "Major career transition",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "There for the big celebrations but also the little things, be consistent is important",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "I''m quiet at first but warm up over time",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Texting throughout the day",\n    "Video calls"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Quick responder, love ongoing conversations",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Need time to process before I am ready to discuss",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "A direct conversation about what happened",\n    "Written communication (text, letter, etc)",\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\n    "Humor and lightness to ease back in"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Stay curious and check in:",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "3",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am learning how to set them, but it''s still hard",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "i tend to withdraw when i feel the other person is very controlling/mean and it can take some time for me to stand up for myself",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Running/Cycling",\n    "Writing (journaling, poetry, books)",\n    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\n    "Fashion/Styling",\n    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\n    "Book clubs or discussion groups",\n    "Volunteering/advocacy",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Reading (fiction, non-fiction, audiobooks)",\n    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\n    "Writing and reflection",\n    "Activism and social change",\n    "Meditation/mindfulness",\n    "Religious gatherings (temple/church/mosque, etc)",\n    "Video games (PC, PS, XBOX, Switch)"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "I am a big crochet/knitter, I aloso am a part time artist (watercolor painting). I love taking art workshops to learn how to make things (rn taking stained glass class)",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Activism",\n    "Empathy",\n    "Creativity",\n    "Trust",\n    "Self-awareness",\n    "Uniqueness",\n    "Vulnerability",\n    "Thrift"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "Friends should be able to have difficult conversations",\n    "Humor and laughter are essential to friendship",\n    "I value friends who share my worldview and values"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Intellectual stimulation",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Adventure and new experiences",\n    "Peaceful, easy presence"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Must love cats (I\u2019m a cat mama), must be free to try new things(foods, activities etc), must be there for the big and the small things",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Unresponsive (I won\u2019t hear from you in 3+ days), not willing to show up for one another, mean/spiteful spirit (hating a celebrity is funny, but not the girl next door\u2026 )",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Words of affirmation (encouragement, posts about you)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Once a week",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Creative",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Easygoing",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Reliable",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "Reliability! Knowing I have something to always turn to for good and bad",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": [\n    "Woman",\n    "Non-binary",\n    "No preference"\n  ],\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "Similar age/life stage (I\u2019m 24 so 22-30 or recent college grad, early career)",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),0,NULL);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(95,144,replace('{\012  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "i\u2019m always looking for more people to mesh with in clt!",\012  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": "Leftist",\012  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\012  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "creative (i make perfumes and i write as well), driven, intriguing, a ball of fun. a true hobby lover.",\012  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "9",\012  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Moderate capacity (I can make time, but need flexibility)",\012  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am actively seeking close, intimate friendships",\012  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\012  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "N/A",\012  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\012  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "showing true curiosity in me, and i\u2019ll return the same. i\u2019m a snail mail type of person, but when i get back to someone, it\u2019ll always be in depth and with serious care involved. and i\u2019ll always make myself available for any emergency situations that would arise as well. vulnerability is important to me too. we don\u2019t have to share everything immediately of course (i\u2019d prefer not to), but i am seeking depth. conversations about ourselves, the world, any interests we have, etc. and doing fun things together as time allows, like museum events or a restaurant date.",\012  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\012  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Somewhere in between \u2013 depends on the vibe",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "4",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "1",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "3",\012  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "2",\012  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\012  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": "Mix of everything/I''m flexible",\012  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\012  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Need time to process before I am ready to discuss",\012  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\012    "A direct conversation about what happened",\012    "Quality time together to reconnect",\012    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology"\012  ],\012  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Address it directly:",\012  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "4",\012  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "I am clear and direct about my boundaries.",\012  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "i used to have a terrible habit of people pleasing, which is something i\u2019m no longer in the business of (and haven\u2019t been for a while). i want to show up as my full and whole self. it feels more beautiful to me that way and you never know who wants to accept the totality of you.",\012  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\012    "Yoga/Pilates",\012    "Dancing (salsa, pole, aerial, casual, etc)",\012    "Sports (playing or watching)",\012    "Writing (journaling, poetry, books)",\012    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\012    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\012    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\012    "Cooking/Baking",\012    "Fashion/Styling",\012    "Book clubs or discussion groups",\012    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\012    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\012    "Reading (fiction, non-fiction, audiobooks)",\012    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\012    "Learning new skills",\012    "Writing and reflection",\012    "Activism and social change",\012    "Meditation/mindfulness",\012    "Tarot/oracle cards",\012    "Astrology",\012    "Therapy/personal growth work",\012    "Nature connection and grounding",\012    "Energy work/holistic practices",\012    "Medicinal herbs/substances"\012  ],\012  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "i am a published writer. i primarily write short stories playing upon magical realism or speculative fiction, with some nonfiction here and there. i make everything as lesbian as possible when i can (i\u2019m lesbian). perfumes and the creation of them are an interest too, though those take more time! \n\nwhen not writing or reading, i like going to: jazz clubs, lounges, events relating to food or music or the arts, museums. cooking is fun too. and, my cats require my time as well. \n\ni love most music but generally stick with soul, jazz, r&amp;b, rap, house, and anything alternative. \n\ni love watching good tv shows or films as well, whatever piques my interest.",\012  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\012  "values_top_values": [\012    "Ambition",\012    "Career",\012    "Social Justice",\012    "Empathy",\012    "Creativity",\012    "Fun",\012    "Spirituality",\012    "Intuition",\012    "Self-expression",\012    "Sexuality"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\012    "Friendship is about celebrating each other''s wins",\012    "Mutual effort and reciprocity matters to me",\012    "I value friends who share my worldview and values"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\012    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\012    "Shared laughter and lightness",\012    "Intellectual stimulation",\012    "Mutual support during hard times",\012    "Celebration of wins and joys",\012    "Accountability and growth",\012    "Consistency and reliability",\012    "Genuineness",\012    "Adventure and new experiences"\012  ],\012  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "empathy, curiosity, the pursuit of knowledge.",\012  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "far too demanding. as an example, i recently tried to make friends with someone who sent me 90 messages, primarily thoughtstream messages, over the span of 12 hours. i have a career plus my hobbies and my cats, and that is way too many for me to keep up with. she was very sweet but even after a few conversations about that, it didn\u2019t improve and it wasn\u2019t sustainable. i\u2019m also not looking to compete with anyone &amp; am not interested in anyone who wants to compete with me. immaturity/lack of self sustainability as well. i understand if someone is trying to get there, but because i have had to be so hyper independent, those who are more reliant on others to get things done for them typically do not mesh well with me. and those that aren\u2019t active listeners, or want to regularly complain about a situation they\u2019re not looking to change. i\u2019m okay with venting but please don\u2019t talk my ear off for hours and days and weeks and months about a partner you\u2019re not leaving. this all sounds rather",\012  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\012    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\012    "Words of affirmation (encouragement, posts about you)",\012    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)"\012  ],\012  "logistics_connection_frequency": "Quality over quantity \u2013 frequency matters less than depth",\012  "logistics_connection_type": "Mix of both",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "vivacious",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "intuitive",\012  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "creative",\012  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "a sense of care.",\012  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": [\012    "Man",\012    "Woman",\012    "Non-binary"\012  ],\012  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "no one under 23!",\012  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\012    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\012    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\012  ]\012}','\012',char(10)),0,NULL);
INSERT INTO assessment VALUES(96,147,replace('{\n  "tell_us_more_what_brings_you": "I just moved back to the area and want to meet like minded friends who want to create art, dance, cook, bake, music and spirituality!",\n  "tell_us_more_political_leanings": [\n    "Liberal",\n    "Apolitical"\n  ],\n  "tell_us_more_gender_identity": "Woman",\n  "tell_us_more_about_yourself": "I\u2019m very flowing but grounded in my energy. I\u2019m more of a wallflower but outgoing when I\u2019m with people that make me feel safe and seen. I love to pour love and intention into my friendships and I\u2019m full of passion for arts, dance and music!",\n  "friendship_readiness_emotional_availability": "10",\n  "friendship_readiness_time_energy_capacity": "Abundant capacity (I have space, time, and energy to invest)",\n  "friendship_readiness_friendship_intention": "I am open to friendships, but want to take it slow",\n  "friendship_readiness_personal_work": "Yes, I''ve worked through a lot in therapy/self-reflection",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances": "N/A",\n  "friendship_readiness_life_circumstances_details": "",\n  "friendship_readiness_showing_up": "In my previous and some current friendships I\u2019m the only one that makes the plans, I\u2019m looking for mutual friendships where we all make plans and equally contribute time and energy into getting to know each other!",\n  "personality_social_style_recharge_style": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_social_settings": "Somewhere in between \u2013 depends on the vibe",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_0": "2",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_1": "1",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_2": "4",\n  "personality_social_style_ideal_hangout_3": "3",\n  "personality_social_style_making_plans": "I like having loose plans but staying flexible",\n  "personality_social_style_communication_preference": [\n    "Occasional meaningful texts",\n    "Mix of everything/I''m flexible"\n  ],\n  "personality_social_style_texting_style": "Thoughtful but slow to respond (hours to days)",\n  "conflict_repair_conflict_response": "Address it directly and as soon as possible",\n  "conflict_repair_repair_looks_like": [\n    "Acknowledgement of impact and sincere apology",\n    "Humor and lightness to ease back in"\n  ],\n  "conflict_repair_flaky_friend_scenario": "Address it directly:",\n  "conflict_repair_feedback_comfort": "5",\n  "conflict_repair_boundary_setting": "It depends on the friendship",\n  "conflict_repair_friendship_lessons": "I\u2019m a giver by nature and I\u2019ve noticed that a lot of friends have taken and taken without giving anything in return. I\u2019ve been doing great recently ending those friendships before it ends up draining me!",\n  "hobbies_interests_activities_interests": [\n    "Hiking/nature walks",\n    "Yoga/Pilates",\n    "Dancing (salsa, pole, aerial, casual, etc)",\n    "Visual arts (painting, drawing, photography)",\n    "Music (playing, creating, deeply listening)",\n    "Crafting (pottery, knitting, DIY, etc)",\n    "Cooking/Baking",\n    "Fashion/Styling",\n    "Hosting gatherings (dinner parties, game nights)",\n    "Attending events (concerts, markets, etc)",\n    "Exploring local spots (cafes, shops)",\n    "Podcasts and documentaries",\n    "Philosophy and deep conversations",\n    "Learning new skills",\n    "Meditation/mindfulness",\n    "Tarot/oracle cards",\n    "Astrology",\n    "Nature connection and grounding",\n    "Energy work/holistic practices",\n    "Medicinal herbs/substances"\n  ],\n  "hobbies_interests_hobbies_details": "",\n  "hobbies_interests_doing_vs_being": "Both",\n  "values_top_values": [\n    "Adventure",\n    "Peace",\n    "Creativity",\n    "Health",\n    "Gratitude",\n    "Spirituality",\n    "Honesty",\n    "Intuition",\n    "Self-awareness",\n    "Self-expression"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_statements_resonate": [\n    "Friends should challenge me to grow",\n    "Humor and laughter are essential to friendship",\n    "Mutual effort and reciprocity matters to me"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_friendship_needs": [\n    "Emotional depth and vulnerability",\n    "Shared laughter and lightness",\n    "Accountability and growth",\n    "Genuineness",\n    "Adventure and new experiences"\n  ],\n  "friendship_values_non_negotiables": "Empathy, laughing, self worth and passion for life, thoughtful",\n  "friendship_values_dealbreakers": "Lying, having a messy/dirty space, being late, not having self discipline or accountability",\n  "friendship_values_connection_language": [\n    "Quality time (hangouts, phone calls, etc)",\n    "Emotional Support (showing up in hard times, being a listening ear)",\n    "Gifts (items that remind them of you)"\n  ],\n  "logistics_connection_frequency": "A few times a month",\n  "logistics_connection_type": "Primarily in-person connections",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word1": "Caring",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word2": "Adventurous",\n  "wrapping_up_ideal_friend_words_word3": "Funny",\n  "wrapping_up_what_want_receive": "I want to share creativity and passions! Create cool things, eat amazing foods, go to events and adventure!",\n  "wrapping_up_gender_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_age_preference": "No preference",\n  "wrapping_up_open_to_multiple_matches": [\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people",\n    "Yes, I''m open to connecting with multiple people"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),1,138);
