INSERT INTO "match" VALUES(20,17,37,8,22,'finalized','Done',NULL,'2026-01-04 23:42:21.599827','2026-01-11 09:22:50.549552',replace('Hi Kallista,\n\nI''m so excited to introduce you to Carousel (she/her)! After carefully reviewing both of your assessments, I have a really good feeling about this match.\n\nHere''s why I think you two will connect:\n\nYou both have moderate capacity for friendship, with the intention of seeking close, intimate friendships. You both also ranked trust in your top values, and you each expressed a desire for friendships where you can show up in all phases of one''s life, whether it be making time for each other, sending voice notes, or holding space for each other. \n\nI noticed that Kallista, you mentioned wanting a friend who is "accepting, non-judgmental, and go with the flow", and Carousel, you described yourself as someone who "is a versatile friend" who values "open-mindedness and lightheartedness". That feels like a beautiful alignment. \n\nYou also have complementary communication styles — Kallista, you''re someone who values transparency and direct communication, and Carousel, you''re someone who may need some time to process, but you''re willing to have that direct communication and transparency. The two of you also value quality time to reconnect and acknowledgment of one''s impact with an apology.  I think you''ll navigate conflict together with a lot of grace.\n\nSome fun overlaps:\n• You both love doing things instead of just being\n• You both enjoy nature walks/hikes, yoga/pilates, crafting, adventure sports, exploring local spots, and learning new skills\n• You both value trust and humor\n• You both enjoy quality time, words of affirmations, voice notes, and emotional support in a friendship \n\nA gentle awareness: Kallista, you mentioned liking plans to be loose and flexible, and Carousel, you tend to prefer concrete plans with minimal wiggle room. This could actually be a beautiful balance if you both communicate openly about your needs!\n\nNext steps: I''ve sent this same message to both of you with each other''s contact info. I encourage you to reach out within the next few days to set up a casual first meeting—coffee, a walk, whatever feels right. You both also RSVP''d for our launch party this Sunday at 1 PM, so this would be a perfect space to start out! :~) \n\nHere are a few more ideas from the Three of Cups team:\n• Sign up for a pottery class together \n• Go climbing together (aerial, rock climbing, etc)\n• Learn a new skill together \n\nContact info:\n• Carousel Sutton (she/her) - carouselsutton@gmail.com\n\nI''m rooting for you both! Remember, not every match will become a lifelong friendship, and that''s okay. Stay open, be yourselves, and see what unfolds. See you two on Sunday!\n\nWith so much hope for beautiful connection,\n\nIris and the Three of Cups Team 🌟','\n',char(10)),replace('Hi Carousel,\n\nI''m so excited to introduce you to Kallista (she/her)! After carefully reviewing both of your assessments, I have a really good feeling about this match.\n\nHere''s why I think you two will connect:\n\nYou both have moderate capacity for friendship, with the intention of seeking close, intimate friendships. You both also ranked trust in your top values, and you each expressed a desire for friendships where you can show up in all phases of one''s life, whether it be making time for each other, sending voice notes, or holding space for each other. \n\nI noticed that Kallista, you mentioned wanting a friend who is "accepting, non-judgmental, and go with the flow", and Carousel, you described yourself as someone who "is a versatile friend" who values "open-mindedness and lightheartedness". That feels like a beautiful alignment. \n\nYou also have complementary communication styles — Kallista, you''re someone who values transparency and direct communication, and Carousel, you''re someone who may need some time to process, but you''re willing to have that direct communication an