atever feels right. You both also RSVP''d for our launch party this Sunday at 1 PM, so this would be a perfect space to start out! :~) \n\nHere are a few more ideas from the Three of Cups team:\n• Go on a walk around Freedom Park together \n• Start a new book together\n• Take a crafty class together \n\nContact info:\n• Elise Lyght (she/her) - elyght2@gmail.com\n\nI''m rooting for you both! Remember, not every match will become a lifelong friendship, and that''s okay. Stay open, be yourselves, and see what unfolds. See you two on Sunday!\n\n\nWith so much hope for beautiful connection,\n\nIris and the Three of Cups Team 🌟','\n',char(10)),replace('Hi Elise,\n\nI''m so excited to introduce you to Kallista (she/her)! After carefully reviewing both of your assessments, I have a really good feeling about this match.\n\nHere''s why I think you two will connect:\n\nYou both are actively seeking close, intimate friendships. You both also ranked genuineness, self-awareness, vulnerability, fun, and empathy in your top values, and expressed wanting a connection where you can both not only hold space for each other, but also try new things together!  \n\nI noticed that Kallista, you mentioned wanting a friend who is accepting and consistent, and Elise, you described yourself as someone who values consistency and reliability. That feels like a beautiful alignment. \n\nYou also have complementary hangout styles — Kallista, you''re someone prefers loose plans with flexibility, along with someone who prefers to text throughout the day and send voice notes. Elise, you also prefer loose plans with flexibility, along with texting and having video calls. While you both prefer in-person hangouts once a week, your ways of communicating in-between hangouts would be a great match. \n\nSome fun overlaps:\n• You both enjoy hiking, yoga, crafting, reading, and learning new skills\n• You both value having fun and being able to laugh together \n• You both enjoy quality time, words of affirmations, voice notes, and emotional support in a friendship \n\nA gentle awareness: Kallista, you mentioned wanting to address any conflict as soon as possible, and Elise, you prefer taking the time to process before you have a discussion. This could actually be a beautiful balance if you both communicate openly about your needs!\n\nNext steps: I''ve sent this same message to both of you with each other''s contact info. I encourage you to reach out within the next few days to set up a casual first meeting—coffee, a walk, whatever feels right. You both also RSVP''d for our launch party this Sunday at 1 PM, so this would be a perfect space to start out! :~) \n\nHere are a few more ideas from the Three of Cups team:\n• Go on a walk around Freedom Park together \n• Start a new book together\n• Take a crafty class together \n\nContact info:\n• Kallista Beeson (she/her) - kallistajeanne@gmail.com\n\nI''m rooting for you both! Remember, not every match will become a lifelong friendship, and that''s okay. Stay open, be yourselves, and see what unfolds. See you two on Sunday!\n\n\nWith so much hope for beautiful connection,\n\nIris and the Three of Cups Team 🌟','\n',char(10)));
INSERT INTO "match" VALUES(24,18,72,55,47,'finalized',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-09 20:18:06.485668','2026-01-11 15:48:10.054781',replace('Hi Alex and Madison,\n\nI''m so excited to introduce you both to each other! Alex, meet Madison (she/her)! Madison, meet Alex (she/her)! While one of your connections is no longer able to make it to the event, I have a really good feeling about this match. \n\nHere''s why I think you two will connect:\nYou both are looking for genuine friendships filled with laughter and authenticity. You both are also looking for someone who is understanding but also has lots of humor and silliness involved. When it comes to non-negotiables, you both value anti-racism and actively working towards justice. \n\nSome fun overlaps:\n• You both enjoy being with others, whether there is an activity involved or not\n• You both enjoy dancing, music, having fun, and finding ways to grow through self/community-directed work or therapy\n• You both value quality time and emotional support as a way to connect in friendship\n\nNext steps: I''ve sent this same message to both of you with each other''s contact info. I encourage you to reach out within the next few days to set up a casual first meeting—coffee, a walk, whatever feels right. You both also RSVP''d for our launch party today at 1 PM, so this would be a perfect space to start out! :~) \n\nHere are a few more ideas from the Three of Cups team:\n• Play "We''re Not Really Strangers" to get to know each other more \n• Go dancing with each other (a class or out and about)\n• Make a playlist for each other\n\n\nContact info:\n• You both are CC''d on this email, so feel free to reach out individually! \n\nI''m rooting for you both! Remember, not every match will become a lifelong friendship, and that''s okay. Stay open, be yourselves, and see what unfolds. See you two soon!\n\n\nWith so much hope for beautiful connection,\n\nIris and The Three of Cups Team 🌟','\n',char(10)),replace('Hi Alex and Madison,\n\nI''m so 