ay open, be yourselves, and see what unfolds. See you two on Sunday!\n\n\nWith so much hope for beautiful connection,\n\nThe Three of Cups Team 🌟','\n',char(10)),replace('Hi Jasmine and Za''Maya,\n\nI''m so excited to introduce you both to each other! Jasmine, meet Za''Maya (she/her)! Za''Maya, meet Jasmine (she/her)! After carefully reviewing both of your assessments, I have a really good feeling about this match.\n\nHere''s why I think you two will connect:\n\nYou both ranked genuineness, activism/justice, and empathy in your top values, and expressed wanting a friendship while taking it slow! \n\nI noticed that Jasmine, you mentioned wanting a friend who is open, stands up for what is right, and understands you, and Za''Maya, you are looking for someone who likes cats (real), values activism and justice, kind, and is fun. That feels like a beautiful alignment. \n\nSome fun overlaps:\n• You both value activism, openness, and quality time \n• You both enjoy hiking/walks, yoga/pilates, dancing, activism, writing, and crafting \n• You both value someone who has a sense of humor and fun\n\nA gentle awareness: Jasmine, while you are willing to travel to Charlotte, there is a bit of a distance from Charlotte to Fayetteville (2 hours isn''t too bad). This distance can be a non-issue, as long as there is planning and intentionality involved! \n\nNext steps: I''ve sent this same message to both of you with each other''s contact info. I encourage you to reach out within the next few days to set up a casual first meeting—coffee, a walk, whatever feels right. You both also RSVP''d for our launch party this Sunday at 1 PM, so this would be a perfect space to start out! :~) \n\nHere are a few more ideas from the Three of Cups team:\n• Cat cafe \n• Learning a new skill together \n• Have a crafting day in the park! \n\nContact info:\n• You both are CC''d on this email, so feel free to reach out individually! \n\nI''m rooting for you both! Remember, not every match will become a l