INSERT INTO "match" VALUES(53,67,24,43,10,'finalized',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-11 09:56:46.902302','2026-01-11 09:57:02.221877',replace('Hi Kavya and Ally,\n\nI''m so excited to introduce you both to each other! Ally, meet Kavya (she/her)! Kavya, meet Ally (she/her)! After carefully reviewing both of your assessments, I have a really good feeling about this match.\n\nHere''s why I think you two will connect:\n\nYou both expressed wanting genuine connections and community. You both also ranked ambition, work ethic/career, intelligence, growth as your top values. You both view friendship is about celebrating each other''s wins with minimal judgment, and want a friend who is part of your support system and can share hobbies with. \n\nI noticed that Ally, you view showing up as the quality of the time you have with someone and value friends who have the ability to show up for each other. Kavya, you''re wanting a friend who is supportive, emotionally intelligent, and uplifting, and quality time is your top connection languages. This feels like a beautiful pairing! \n\nSome fun overlaps:\n• You both prefer having loose plans with flexibility \n• You both enjoy cooking/baking, exploring local spots, attending events, and are invested in your personal growth \n• You both value quality time and emotional support \n\n\nA gentle awareness: Kavya can have a busy work schedule, but has more flexibility on the weeks, and Ally is currently going through a career transition. This could actually work beautifully if navigated with intentionality, communication, and openness. \n\nNext steps: I''ve sent this same message to both of you with each other''s contact info. I encourage you to reach out within the next few days to set up a casual first meeting—coffee, a walk, whatever feels right. You both also RSVP''d for our launch party this Sunday at 1 PM, so this would be a perfect space to start out! :~) \n\nHere are a few more ideas from the Three of Cups team:\n• Play "We''re Not Really Strangers" together \n• Explore each other''s favorite spot in Charlotte together \n• Share a hobby with each other that may be different from the other''s \n\nContact info:\n• You both are CC''d on this email, so feel free to reach out individually! \n\nI''m rooting for you both! Remember, not every match will become a lifelong friendship, and that''s okay. Stay open, be yourselves, and see what unfolds. See you two on Sunday!\n\n\nWith so much hope for beautiful connection,\n\nIris and The Three of Cups Team 🌟','\n',char(10)),replace('Hi Kavya and Ally,\n\nI''m so excited to introduce you both to each other! Ally, meet Kavya (she/her)! Kavya, meet Ally (she/her)! After carefully reviewing both of your assessments, I have a really good feeling about this match.\n\nHere''s why I think you two will connect:\n\nYou both expressed wanting genuine connections and community. You both also ranked ambition, work ethic/career, intelligence, growth as your top values. You both view friendship is about celebrating each other''s wins with minimal judgment, and want a friend who is part of your support system and can share hobbies with. \n\nI noticed that Ally, you view showing up as the quality of the time you have with someone and value friends who have the ability to show up for each other. Kavya, you''re wanting a friend who is supportive, emotionally intelligent, and uplifting, and quality time is your top connection languages. This feels like a beautiful pairing! \n\nSome fun overlaps:\n• You both prefer having loose plans with flexibility \n• You both enjoy cooking/baking, exploring local spots, attending events, and are invested in your personal growth \n• You both value quality time and emotional support \n\n\nA gentle awareness: Kavya can have a busy work schedule, but has more flexibility on the weeks, and Ally is currently going through a career transition. This could actually work beautifully if navigated with intentionality, communication, and openness. \n\nNext step